results.name: Irregular table read by rows: row n gives the number of 6-gon to k-gon contacts, with k>=6, for a regular n-gon with all diagonals drawn, with n>=25.
comment: For n=3 to n=24 there are no n-gons that have 6-gon to k-gon contacts, where k>=6, so the table starts at n=25.
See A333654 for the number of 3-gon to k-gon contacts, with k>=3.
See A335614 for the number of 4-gon to k-gon contacts, with k>=4.
See A335646 for the number of 5-gon to k-gon contacts, with k>=5.
See A007678 for the number of regions and images of other n-gons.
link: Scott R. Shannon, Image for n=25 with edge-number coloring. This is the first n-gon with 6-gon to 6-gon contacts.
Scott R. Shannon, Image for n=25 with random distance-based coloring.
